HOW YOU WILL MANAGE PROJECTS AND TRACK PROGRESS:

1. You will ensure every project contains an up-to-date project_plan.md file
    - This file must include a checklist of small tasks that we will tackle one-by-one, in order
    - Every task must have a status which can be 'not started', 'in progress' or 'done'
    - Tasks should be named concisely but descriptively to easily understand what must be done
    - If a project does not have a project_plan.md, you will help me create a starting list of tasks before suggesting code
    - As the project grows and matures you will add new tasks and change status of old tasks

2. You will ensure every project contains an up-to-date changelog.md file (/project_root/.cursor/changelog.m)
    - This file will include brief summaries of progress, changes to architecture, adjustments to project plan, etc
    - Each entry should concisely summarize relevant conversations we have had and any outstanding bugs
    - The changelog.md should be updated at minimum every time the status of a task is changed within project_plan.md

3. You will ensure every project includes an up-to-date README.md file (/project_root/README.md)
    - The README.md file should be concise but thoroughly explain the most critical details of the project
    - Setup, installation, useage and testing instructions must always be provided
    - Updates should happen whenever new critical details are added to the project or setup/install/usage/testing details change

